don't know if it's similar in Europe, but
I'm just kind of curious of why you think

01:00:23.589 --> 01:00:25.430
there are certain subjects that are stressed
more to younger individuals as they're going

01:00:25.430 --> 01:00:26.430
up. And, you know, something like philosophy
that seems very important to me, and what

01:00:26.430 --> 01:00:29.730
do you think if anything can be done about
that?

01:00:29.730 --> 01:00:34.690
&gt;&gt; ZIZEK: Oh, my god. This is a big question
because my first reaction is that you know

01:00:34.690 --> 01:00:39.749
that in the last years, unfortunately, because
I think this is a good thing in Europe. The

01:00:39.749 --> 01:00:44.989
key, I think, is--one good thing about Europe--you
in the United States you have elementary school

01:00:44.989 --> 01:00:49.359
and you come out, is it nine or ten years?
And then you have this college, two years

01:00:49.359 --> 01:00:55.170
or whatever and you go to university, but
in Europe, this two years expand into four,

01:00:55.170 --> 01:01:01.049
we call it, lyceum, gymnasium, high school.
