01:01:52.599 --> 01:01:58.140
analysis that I made through that glasses,
it brings out some very funny results. For

01:01:58.140 --> 01:02:05.469
example, I was always perplexed by the standard
Catholic answer, which is don't mess biogenetically

01:02:05.469 --> 01:02:12.459
with brain because if you do it, you diminish
man to a biological animal, but we have immortal

01:02:12.459 --> 01:02:18.759
soul, blah, blah. My god, my problem here
was--wait a minute, if you believe we have

01:02:18.759 --> 01:02:24.239
an immortal soul, what's then the problem
with messing with brain? I mean I cannot touch

01:02:24.239 --> 01:02:30.209
the soul. So I think the true message in between
lines of this Catholic anti--anti-biogenetic

01:02:30.209 --> 01:02:39.150
brain sciences experiment is a different one.
It's a--let's--it's better not to know some

01:02:39.150 --> 01:02:47.400
things. Let’s avoid knowing that because
knowing too much there may deprive us of our

01:02:47.400 --> 01:02:53.269
dignity, may diminish our freedom and so on
and so on. So, again, it's not only this.

01:02:53.269 --> 01:02:58.249
It's other prob--where I think effectively
that we are at such a crucial moment, now,

01:02:58.249 --> 01:03:04.619
truly, not in the religious sense of a catastrophe
but in a sense of apocalyptic moment that

01:03:04.619 --> 01:03:07.910
we have to make decisions which are much more
radical.

01:03:07.910 --> 01:03:16.069
&gt;&gt; Thank you for coming today. I had a question
about how you normally respond to claims that

01:03:16.069 --> 01:03:21.380
Marxism and radicalism is dead?
&gt;&gt; ZIZEK: I mean, no, mystery here and the

01:03:21.380 --> 01:03:26.299
mystery is rather this one to put--I will
be very short. Why do I consider myself still

01:03:26.299 --> 01:03:31.949
some kind of a Marxist without any illusions
and so on. Look, the question we have today

01:03:31.949 --> 01:03:36.779
is that--the only serious question is this
one. Is Fukuyama Francis, right or not? Even

01:03:36.779 --> 01:03:43.319
most of today's left, isn’t did there are
Fukuyamaists as it were? They basically adapt

01:03:43.319 --> 01:03:49.059
liberal democracy, some kind of capitalism
as if not the best at least the least worst,

01:03:49.059 --> 01:03:53.229
the least bad system, and yet, the idea is
just--you know, when I was young we’ll have

01:03:53.229 --> 01:03:57.829
a saying, we want socialism with a human face.
What even the left today basically offers

01:03:57.829 --> 01:04:03.519
is global capitalism with the human face.
Make it a little bit better as Bill Gates

01:04:03.519 --> 01:04:07.150
would put it, create this capitalism. You
can have your cake and it eat it, you can

01:04:07.150 --> 01:04:13.429
have profit and help the poor, whatever, to
make it more. So my question is, is this all?

01:04:13.429 --> 01:04:21.440
Is this our ultimate horizons? Or are there
crises, antagonisms on the horizon? Which

01:04:21.440 --> 01:04:28.359
for which in the long term--and by long term,
I don't mean this 200 years, but 10, 15 years,

01:04:28.359 --> 01:04:34.009
20, global capitalism will not be enough to
solve them. I think there are from biogenetics,

01:04:34.009 --> 01:04:39.289
even Francis Fukuyama, you know, his next
book on human freedom or whatever, he explicitly

01:04:39.289 --> 01:04:45.559
says that this biogenetic possibilities undermine
his vision of global capitalism, that one.

01:04:45.559 --> 01:04:51.529
Then ecology, I claim and so on, so I think
if you want to know my argument in detail,

01:04:51.529 --> 01:04:55.519
now, I will do an unfair thing and refer to
an another book of mine, In Defense of Lost

01:04:55.519 --> 01:05:02.079
Causes, in the last chapter, I try precisely
to argue where I see and only in this sense,

01:05:02.079 --> 01:05:09.019
I'm a Marxist. I claim, let's not be so sure,
this liberal democratic capitalism, maybe

01:05:09.019 --> 01:05:15.740
is not the ultimate horizon. We should just
keep our mind open. I'm not now saying of

01:05:15.740 --> 01:05:20.609
course, oh, will there be--that there will
be a new Leninist party or whatever, no, that

01:05:20.609 --> 01:05:26.589
is over. But we should, that's the limit of
my Marxism. I even don't see a solution because,

01:05:26.589 --> 01:05:32.249
you know, all Marxist--always have this satisfaction
the train of history is on my side or should

01:05:32.249 --> 01:05:37.460
I put it, you know, like we are just realizing
historical necessity, no, I don't think. I'm

01:05:37.460 --> 01:05:42.489
only saying I see ominous signs here and there,
and I want that if global capitalism will

01:05:42.489 --> 01:05:48.179
be able to cope with it in the long terms.
One of the problem, I see purely economic

01:05:48.179 --> 01:05:53.269
is the one with which you are dealing a lot,
you again, as Googlers, namely, the problem

01:05:53.269 --> 01:05:58.890
of intellectual property. I think that more
and more it's exploding as a problem because

01:05:58.890 --> 01:06:03.709
I think that intellectual property if you
pardon me the expression is in its nature

01:06:03.709 --> 01:06:10.349
closer to communism than to capitalism. You
have to force it. It's very difficult to contain

01:06:10.349 --> 01:06:16.579
it within the limits of private property,
which is why you get all these paradoxes.

01:06:16.579 --> 01:06:25.309
If you allow too strong logic of private property
to determine the domain of knowledge, intellectual

01:06:25.309 --> 01:06:30.179
achievements, then you get somebody like Bill
Gates. I have nothing against him; I'm just

01:06:30.179 --> 01:06:36.150
saying that if you have a guy who in 30 years
becomes from a nobody, tinkering in his garage,

01:06:36.150 --> 01:06:42.640
to the richest man on the earth. Doesn’t
this show that market mechanism, you cannot

01:06:42.640 --> 01:06:48.400
in any way say that, his wealth reflect his
achievement or how should I put it, you know,

01:06:48.400 --> 01:06:53.920
it's just market cannot reflect it properly.
So that would be my answer, but read the book,

01:06:53.920 --> 01:07:00.799
I talk too much. Now, aha, you want it balanced,
left, right, left, right, okay, right again.

01:07:00.799 --> 01:07:03.839
Okay.
&gt;&gt; I've enjoyed your talk very much; I came

01:07:03.839 --> 01:07:07.859
a little bit late, so I didn’t hear whether
you said anything about it, but I was wondering

01:07:07.859 --> 01:07:14.459
if you've used the toilets here at Google?
We have an optical sensor in our toilets.

01:07:14.459 --> 01:07:18.710
&gt;&gt; ZIZEK: What do they--does it do?
&gt;&gt; Well, when you stand up, it flushes.

01:07:18.710 --> 01:07:21.669
&gt;&gt; ZIZEK: Yeah, I'm used to them from the
airport and here.

01:07:21.669 --> 01:07:24.680
&gt;&gt; You get up and you don’t have to touch
anything and I was wondering if--to me it

01:07:24.680 --> 01:07:31.289
seems that we have some sort of ideology here
that technology will address even the most

01:07:31.289 --> 01:07:36.609
fundamental human problems and will sort of
transform us and I was wondering…

01:07:36.609 --> 01:07:42.559
&gt;&gt; ZIZEK: No, no, no, what my answer here
would just have been--no, maybe I am too naïve,

01:07:42.559 --> 01:07:48.890
utilitarian, but my--I always thought that
they come up with this, because people care

01:07:48.890 --> 01:07:54.609
about bacteria with that and the point is
rather I think, how to prevent you touching

01:07:54.609 --> 01:07:59.809
something. Wasn’t this the origin was to
keep you--so it's a--but on the other hand,

01:07:59.809 --> 01:08:05.019
I agree with you and I've seen even--no, this
is, I mean there it's to go on and on, for

01:08:05.019 --> 01:08:10.640
example, in Japan, I was told, you know, that
it's also a nice cultural detail that in many

01:08:10.640 --> 01:08:19.199
public toilets, so I was told, there is music
while you are shitting on the toilet, why?

01:08:19.199 --> 01:08:24.889
Because people are so sensitive and embarrassed
by potential sounds you make while you are

01:08:24.889 --> 01:08:30.000
shitting and so on. So the idea is the only
way to make it tolerable is to have a background

01:08:30.000 --> 01:08:37.589
of music enough, and so on, and so on. So,
I totally—how should I put it--maybe even

01:08:37.589 --> 01:08:42.429
more than eating, shitting is a measure of
civilization. In the sense of, if you want

01:08:42.429 --> 01:08:48.400
to see the basic of a civilization, it's not
look at how people eat, look at how people

01:08:48.400 --> 01:08:54.679
shit. The true color for me would have been
in--and I read somewhere, there are already,

01:08:54.679 --> 01:09:00.469
the plans which are even worse that--sorry
for vulgarity, you will not even have to do

01:09:00.469 --> 01:09:07.949
that the--sorry, obscene gestures to press
the shit out. That there is some kind of vacuums

01:09:07.949 --> 01:09:13.380
stuff, you know and so, it will just be done
for you, totally, how that would we know.

01:09:13.380 --> 01:09:20.259
That will be pretty terrible, I mean, no?
But again, yes--again, I love details like

01:09:20.259 --> 01:09:25.039
this, because I think that through them, you
get that ideology, which is like for example

01:09:25.039 --> 01:09:30.889
in my books, I love another detail. Did you
notice for example, if you know a little bit

01:09:30.889 --> 01:09:35.140
about history of totalitarianism and how,
if you look at Hitler when he speaks or a

01:09:35.140 --> 01:09:40.969
Fascist leader, people applaud; Hitler accepts
the applause. Look at the communist leaders

01:09:40.969 --> 01:09:48.190
speaking, people applause, what does the communist
do? Stands up and joins the applause. This

01:09:48.190 --> 01:09:53.870
tells everything, it's totally different logic,
Stalin is dictator, is not a master, it's

01:09:53.870 --> 01:09:59.380
a perfect servant of the people. It's always,
I'm not thinking myself, I'm only you, and

01:09:59.380 --> 01:10:05.239
it points out a totally different logic, which
can be substantiated by the other claims.

01:10:05.239 --> 01:10:11.909
For example, I write in a book on Upper Bamum
Gulag, that every year on Stalin's birthday,

01:10:11.909 --> 01:10:17.320
all the arrested in Gulag, all the people
imprisoned there where collected, even in

01:10:17.320 --> 01:10:22.230
the darkest years of Stalinism, were assembled
and have to sign a telegram, wishing Comrade

01:10:22.230 --> 01:10:27.260
Stalin all the best for birthday, and wishing
him greater, even success in building socialism

01:10:27.260 --> 01:10:35.139
and so on. Now think about it, you cannot
even imagine the same thing in Fascism. Well,

01:10:35.139 --> 01:10:40.170
together all the Jews in Auschwitz and make
them, all the best wishes telegram to Hitler

01:10:40.170 --> 01:10:45.010
and so on. You see, I love these details,
like your electronic toilet, or whatever,

01:10:45.010 --> 01:10:51.940
which, you know, a small meaningless feature,
but like crystal, it shows, it condenses a

01:10:51.940 --> 01:10:59.210
fundamental difference. You know, sorry to…
&gt;&gt; So, you give a great example about how

01:10:59.210 --> 01:11:05.350
the TV is a proxy for our laughter, so I'm
going to ask an obvious question, what do

01:11:05.350 --> 01:11:10.409
you--what is God essentially a proxy for or
do you use Him or Her for?

01:11:10.409 --> 01:11:12.270
&gt;&gt; ZIZEK: God?
&gt;&gt; Yes.

01:11:12.270 --> 01:11:20.130
&gt;&gt; ZIZEK: It all depends on what we--on, I
mean, first I don’t think there is one God,

01:11:20.130 --> 01:11:25.829
I mean, I'm an atheist, so, sorry. So, if
we talk about God, of course, it's about how

01:11:25.829 --> 01:11:33.599
God functions, as an idea, representation
and so on and so on. I think God is many things,

01:11:33.599 --> 01:11:40.289
but I think, what God is--it's a very nice
question that you ask, because I think that

01:11:40.289 --> 01:11:50.139
God is at its most fundamental and radical,
not so much a determinant proxy, but the very

01:11:50.139 --> 01:11:56.570
structure of having a proxy. God is the original
proxy, I don’t know, but He knows for me.

01:11:56.570 --> 01:12:03.659
I don’t but He does in Christ. I'm not compassionate
enough, you know, God is this very formal

01:12:03.659 --> 01:12:08.860
structure, it is by alone anything. I don’t
think we can get over God as simple as that.

01:12:08.860 --> 01:12:14.420
There is in the very structure of language
not that shit about, is there a gene for emotions

01:12:14.420 --> 01:12:21.940
of God? But more in a purely semantic way;
the moment we are in language, there is a

01:12:21.940 --> 01:12:27.130
divine dimension that we presuppose it, that
we practice it in a way. So, again, I would

01:12:27.130 --> 01:12:34.099
say, God is originally this very dimension
of having a proxy, or how should I put it.

01:12:34.099 --> 01:12:40.699
And it’s original, this dimension. I don’t
think there ever was originally, a humanity

01:12:40.699 --> 01:12:45.381
which fully lost itself. No, it's from the
beginning that we have these gaps. What do

01:12:45.381 --> 01:12:49.770
I mean by this? Let's take a little--let's
say we are half-French, I see you, I stumble

01:12:49.770 --> 01:12:55.929
on you tomorrow on the street here and we
say can’t--and I tell you, nice to meet

01:12:55.929 --> 01:13:02.370
you, how are you? We both know that probably,
I'm in a way, lying. First, I don’t really

01:13:02.370 --> 01:13:07.570
care how are you, if I were really to give
a full right to tell me to F... off. It's

01:13:07.570 --> 01:13:13.349
none of your business how I am. Or--but you
know what I mean, we--it's a lie, but it's

01:13:13.349 --> 01:13:19.940
a sincere lie. It's wrong to say hypocrisy.
So I don’t think that we have to presuppose

01:13:19.940 --> 01:13:25.350
that there was an original, phenomenal, logical
moment when--when people said, "How are you?"

01:13:25.350 --> 01:13:31.440
They really meant it, authentically. No, the
gap is--from the very beginning here, others--others

01:13:31.440 --> 01:13:39.000
believe for you, others feel for you and God
would have been--God is this very other dimension,

01:13:39.000 --> 01:13:45.070
there has to be what Jacques Lacan calls--Jacques
Lacan precisely calls this dimension the Big

01:13:45.070 --> 01:13:49.389
Upper. The one for whom we have to maintain
appearances and so on and so on. So, yes,

01:13:49.389 --> 01:13:54.889
it's a very nice question and I love to dwell
on this, all these, thanks very much.

01:13:54.889 --> 01:14:00.130
&gt;&gt; Thank you so much for coming it's been
fascinating. Google famously has an informal

01:14:00.130 --> 01:14:03.709
motto, "Don't be Evil," as the next tunnel
observer, what do you think our unknown knowns

01:14:03.709 --> 01:14:10.239
are?
&gt;&gt; ZIZEK: No, I'm not saying that the true

01:14:10.239 --> 01:14:16.400
message is--it’s not simply like, oh, in
a Freudian way, you know, when you say, this

01:14:16.400 --> 01:14:21.340
woman is not my mother then Freud said, ha,
ha, ha, the negation, blah, blah. So I'm not

01:14:21.340 --> 01:14:27.590
saying that you are fundamentally evil. But
what does interest me is what is the model

01:14:27.590 --> 01:14:34.550
of evil which is presupposed in it, nonetheless
the inherent logic is that, you know, because

01:14:34.550 --> 01:14:41.550
why warn them precisely against this? What
is the model of evil here? What is--why the

01:14:41.550 --> 01:14:49.139
need to react against this? I think it's not--these
kinds of injunctions are never general injunctions.

01:14:49.139 --> 01:14:54.489
Like of course, nobody should be evil. No,
but which is evil is there? It is--I don’t

01:14:54.489 --> 01:14:59.219
know, you leave the perception, but you, being
the most powerful search machine and so on,

01:14:59.219 --> 01:15:03.679
are open to the temptation of manipulation,
I don’t know. The question to be asks would

01:15:03.679 --> 01:15:12.801
have been, what dimension of evil? On the
other hand, generally, I think that in a way

01:15:12.801 --> 01:15:20.270
evil is good. No, no, I'm not part of some
crazy, pseudo-dialectic. What I'm saying is

01:15:20.270 --> 01:15:27.059
that, what is evil? Evil is something which
as it were brutally interrupts the normal

01:15:27.059 --> 01:15:33.360
run of things. Evil is a cut and so on, which
is right, for example, for traditional pagan

01:15:33.360 --> 01:15:39.210
religions, Jesus Christ is evil embodied and
in a way, they are right. Because the message

01:15:39.210 --> 01:15:45.570
of Christianity is--it's over with that karma,
everything circulates and so on; it’s a

01:15:45.570 --> 01:15:53.949
cut. So I claim that this, "Don’t be Evil,"
it's more like, we are doing something terribly

01:15:53.949 --> 01:16:00.179
great, let's not do it too fast or whatever.
And I totally, accept this, I think. I totally

01:16:00.179 --> 01:16:06.280
accept this, what you are doing is evil, which
means, it shakes things the way they were.

01:16:06.280 --> 01:16:12.460
I mean, something, you are doing something
which is in a way crazy. You also are changing

01:16:12.460 --> 01:16:18.059
what means being human. I mean, you know,
how it changes our perception that basically,

01:16:18.059 --> 01:16:22.360
if we are not a total idiot, I'm close to
it, but hope not totally total, like, you

01:16:22.360 --> 01:16:27.170
know, it's no longer that by bibliography,
whatever, you get everything. This life in

01:16:27.170 --> 01:16:36.310
a permanent presence as it were, no? So, I
would say that it's a negative recognition

01:16:36.310 --> 01:16:42.150
that there is a radical dimension to what
you are doing. It affects the normal community

01:16:42.150 --> 01:16:49.800
life, and so on, and so on. And my conclusion
is that, in order to say don’t be evil,

01:16:49.800 --> 01:16:59.780
you must already dwell in that space of evil
and I congratulate you for it. Thank you very

01:16:59.780 --> 01:17:01.329
much.

